    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a museum-quality 2004 Porsche 911 Turbo, featuring the revered 3.6L Mezger flat-six engine. This power plant, derived from the GT1 racing program, utilizes a true dry-sump lubrication system and avoids the IMS bearing concerns of its naturally aspirated counterparts. The twin K16 turbochargers spool effortlessly, showing zero boost lag or shaft play, while the G96/50 six-speed manual transmission offers precise, tactile gate engagement. The chassis is anchored by the M030 sport suspension, with all bushings and subframe connectors in factory-fresh state. The undercarriage is remarkably clean, free of any fluid seepage or oxidative scaling on the exhaust manifolds. This example retains its original structural rigidity and performance envelope, presenting an interior with no bolster compression and a dashboard free of UV degradation. A turn-key investment for the discerning enthusiast seeking peak 996-era engineering.",
